                         WG21/X3J16 Meeting Information
                                9-14 March 1997


          Digital Equipment Corporation is pleased to host the March
          1997 meeting of WG21/X3J16.

          Location:      Crowne Plaza Hotel
                         2 Somerset Parkway
                         Nashua, New Hampshire 03063-1036
                         USA

          Hotel Phones:  1-800-962-7482
                         +1-603-886-1200
                         +1-603-595-4199 (Fax)

          Important:     State that you are attending the WG21/Digital
                         meeting in order to get the special room
                         rates!  Verify you are getting the rates
                         below when you make your reservation.

          Room Rates:    $63.00 Single Occupancy
                         $73.00 Double Occupancy
                         $85.00 Concierge Single
                         $95.00 Concierge Double
                         plus 8% New Hampshire State Tax
                         (Concierge rooms are luxury rooms with
                         whirlpool baths, etc)

          Cutoff Date:   Please reserve your room by 17 February 1997.

          Airports:      You can fly into either the Manchester, New
                         Hampshire airport or the Boston,
                         Massachusetts airport.  I strongly recommend
                         Manchester Airport.

                         Manchester Airport is about 30 minutes away
                         from the hotel.  The hotel provides a free
                         shuttle service to and from Manchester
                         Airport from 7 AM to 11 PM (there is a $20
                         charge outside of those hours).  The hotel
                         requests that you reserve a seat on the
                         shuttle by calling the hotel's reservation
                         desk in advance once you know your flight
                         information.  The hotel does have courtesy
                         telephones in the luggage pickup area of the
                         airport.  However, if you wait until reaching
                         the airport before requesting shuttle
                         service, there may be a long delay before you
                         can be picked up.

                         Boston Airport (Logan Airport) is 60 to 90
                         minutes away from the hotel.  Boston traffic
                         near the airport is frequently heavy and the
                         roads can be tricky to navigate.  The hotel
                         does not provide free transportation to/from
                         Boston Airport.  There are two commercial
                         shuttle services:

                         M and L Transportation.  Cost:  $26/person
                         one way.  Hours:  8 AM to 11 PM (10 PM on
                         Saturday).  Major Credit Cards accepted.
                         Call 938-8646 once you arrive at the airport
                         to be picked up.  To reserve a return trip
                         from the hotel to the airport, call
                         1-800-225-4846 the day before leaving.

                         Flight Line.  Cost:  $26/person one way.
                         Hours:  9 AM to 11 PM (or anytime with a
                         reservation).  Reservations requested, call
                         1-800-245-2525 or +1-603-893-8254.  Cash or
                         Traveler's checks only.

          Car:           A car is unnecessary.  The hotel has two
                         restaurants, and six other restaurants are
                         within a five to ten minute walk.

                         If you would like to rent a car while at the
                         hotel, the hotel can arrange for Budget
                         Rent-a-car to deliver and pick up a car.

          Hotel
          Facilities:    Modular plugs on phones for modems.  Full
                         Health Club with free weights, Nautilus
                         machine, indoor pool, outdoor tennis (see
                         weather).  Laundry and Dry Cleaning Service.

          Weather:       During March, below freezing temperatures are
                         common.  Typically, snow is upon the ground.
                         Large snow storms that disrupt air travel are
                         possible.  (Hey, I tried to volunteer for a
                         Summer meeting.)

          Problems/
          Questions:     Randy Meyers
